Get a Customs Declaration

get

/customsDeclarations/{gtmTransactionGid}

Request

Path Parameters
  • gtmTransactionGid(required): string
    Resource ID
Query Parameters
  • expand: string
    Comma-delimited string of child resource names that you want to expand so that the contents return with the parent in the same GET request.
  • fields: string
    Comma-delimited string of field names that you wanted returned in a GET request.

There's no request body for this operation.

Supported Media Types
  • application/vnd.oracle.resource+json;type=singular

  • carrierCode: string
    The carrier code.
  • conveyanceFlag: string
    Flag of the vessel used for the border movement GTM trade transaction.
  • conveyanceName: string
    Name of the vessel used for the border movement GTM trade transaction.
  • countryOfExport: string
    This describes the country of export for the transaction.
  • countryOfImport: string
    This describes the country of import for the transaction.
  • currencyGid: string
    The currency in which values should be sent for filing. It is foreign key reference to CURRENCY table.
  • dataQueryTypeGid: string
    A data query type represents different business objects.
  • departTransportModeGid: string
    The departure transport mode. Which is a foreign key to TRANSPORT_MODE table.
  • departureConveyanceFlag: string
    The departure conveyance flag.
  • departureConveyanceName: string
    The departure conveyance name.
  • documents: documents
  • domainName: string
    Database domain where this data is stored.
  • exchangeRateDate: exchangeRateDate
    The Exchange Rate date to be used for value conversion while preparing the declaration.
  • exchangeRateGid: string
    The Exchange Rate ID to be used for value conversion while preparing the declaration. It is foreign key reference to EXCHANGE_RATE table.
  • gtmBondGid: string
    The bond or guarantee used for the import duties and taxes of the GTM trade transaction.
  • gtmDeclarationTypeGid: string
    The declaration type ID across all domains. Which is a foreign key to GTM_DECLARATION_TYPE table.
  • gtmDeclSTypeGid: string
    The Declaration Sub Type ID. It is foreign key reference to GTM_DECL_S_TYPE table.
  • gtmPriorProcedureGid: string
    Specifies the previous customs procedure that occurred before the current one. For example, before your goods are released for free circulation, they may have entered a bonded warehouse first. This field is used to indicate the entry into the bonded warehouse. It is a foreign key reference to GTM_PROCEDURE.
  • gtmProcedureDetailGid: string
    The procedure detail GID.
  • gtmProcedureGid: string
    This is the customs procedure being requested for this declaration. Examples include Inward Processing Procedure in the EU or Consumption - Foreign Trade Zone in the US. It is a foreign key to GTM_PROCEDURE.
  • gtmTradePreferenceGid: string
    The Trade Preference ID which is the tariff treatment of the goods. It is a foreign key reference to GTM_TRADE_PREFERENCE table.
  • gtmTransactionGid: string
    The GID for the GTM trade transaction.
  • gtmTransactionXid: string
    The external identifier (XID) for the GTM trade transaction.
  • gtmValuationMethodGid: string
    The valuation method ID.
  • incoTermGid: string
    Incoterm used for the GTM trade transaction. It is a foreign key reference to the INCO_TERM table.
  • incoTermLocation: string
    Incoterm location used for the GTM trade transaction.
  • inlandConveyanceFlag: string
    The inland conveyance flag.
  • inlandConveyanceName: string
    The inland conveyance name.
  • inlandTransportModeGid: string
    The inland transport mode. Which is a foreign key to TRANSPORT_MODE table.
  • insertDate: insertDate
    Read Only: true
    insert date
  • involvedLocations: involvedLocations
  • involvedParties: involvedParties
  • isHazardousCargo: boolean
    Indicates if the goods on the GTM trade transaction are hazardous.
  • isTemplate: boolean
    Checkbox indicating whether this GTM transaction or declaration record will be used as a template.
  • lines: lines
  • links: array links
    Read Only: true
  • logicConfigGid: string
    The declaration configuration details that were used to build declaration from transactions or transaction lines.
  • objectId: string
    The object ID.
  • policies: policies
  • ports: ports
  • refnums: refnums
  • remarks: remarks
  • reqBsStatusCodeGid: string
    This column refers to the Status Code of the request for customs filing of a declaration. It is a foreign key reference to the BS_STATUS_CODE table.
  • reqBsStatusGroupGid: string
    This column refers to the Status Group of the request status of custom filing of a declaration. It is a foreign key reference to the BS_STATUS_GROUP table.
  • reqdocs: reqdocs
  • respBsStatusCodeGid: string
    This column refers to the Status Code of the response received after customs filing of a declaration. It is a foreign key reference to the BS_STATUS_CODE table.
  • respBsStatusGroupGid: string
    This column refers to the Status Group of the response status received after custom filing of a declaration. It is a foreign key reference to the BS_STATUS_GROUP table.
  • statuses: statuses
  • transactionCodes: transactionCodes
  • transactionDates: transactionDates
  • transactionQuantities: transactionQuantities

    Read Only: true
    update date
